32:32.384 --> 32:50.342
of the United States. And McNamara

32:52.064 --> 32:59.792
received much criticism, very little praise.

33:02.388 --> 33:31.230
But overall,

33:02.388 --> 33:31.230
you have to give the man credit for fostering what 
the Colonel DeVolt had attempted to do by starting

33:02.388 --> 33:31.230
to build a conventional deterrent and to maintain 
some balance in the strategic deterrent and

33:33.134 --> 33:59.901
modernizing the theater nuclear deterrent and at 
the same time fighting a war in Vietnam and trying

33:33.134 --> 33:59.901
to fight that war and his theory was we ought to end 
that war

33:33.134 --> 33:59.901
with not one nickel spent beyond what it cost to run 
that war in other words When the war is over, when

34:00.843 --> 34:11.014
the ceasefire comes, or whatever it is, whoever 
wins, loses, or draws, the inventory should be

34:00.843 --> 34:11.014
zero at that point in time. Of course, that's where 
I disagreed with him, because that indicates that

34:11.194 --> 34:22.847
that is the last of all wars, in which it's wrong, in 
which your security capability drops back to

34:11.194 --> 34:22.847
zero. And you can't afford that. But that's the 
dollar aspect of it. What kind of person was he? Can

34:35.332 --> 34:40.658
you give me sort of a description of his character?

34:40.678 --> 34:42.680
I think he liked a lot of independence. He didn't 
like too many people around. I think he

34:45.142 --> 34:54.992
had utter disregard for people. I mean he had no 
sense of feeling for people at all. They were just

34:58.673 --> 35:00.115
something else. They were tools.

35:04.662 --> 35:12.274
No sense of feeling for people, and no sense of 
respect for the political side of America. He

35:12.294 --> 35:22.850
thought the politicians are all little gimmicks, 
or he thought of things, you know,

35:12.294 --> 35:22.850
insignificance, and that sort of thing. And that 
caused him a lot of misery. But that's, when you

35:26.415 --> 35:27.617
treat them, When you treat the politicians as a 
bunch of little kids, you know, that you can slap

35:28.222 --> 35:40.754
and kick around, or dogs, that's what you get. 
You're asking for it. Absolutely. And he got it.

35:46.920 --> 35:47.921
But I liked the man. He never harmed me. He'd only 
help. He had very high standards of performance.

35:58.495 --> 36:01.458
And anybody that performed well stayed there. 
General Haig was there as lieutenant colonel. I

36:07.003 --> 36:08.084
was there as a colonel. Alexander Haig was there as 
a lieutenant colonel? Oh yeah. Oh yeah. He worked

36:15.431 --> 36:21.957
for Mr. Joe Califano, who was chief special 
assistant to Mr. McNamara. And that's when I

36:21.977 --> 36:25.941
learned, that's when I knew Joe Califano. What did 
you think of him? Just one hell of a guy. Smart, just

36:30.958 --> 36:34.202
a tremendous guy. What did you think of Haig? 
Phenomenal lieutenant commander and battalion

36:36.946 --> 36:42.914
commander. He was one of my battalion commanders 
in Vietnam in my division, Division G3, Chief of

36:42.954 --> 36:51.646
Operations as a lieutenant colonel. And he was 
really good? Oh, absolutely. Absolutely best.

36:58.216 --> 36:59.939
Absolutely the best. Why? Smart, very intense 
from the standpoint of learning and retention,

37:01.601 --> 37:21.191
burning desire to succeed, warm personality, 
respectful of others, seniors and subordinates

37:01.601 --> 37:21.191
alike. Hello, man. I saw him there. Oh, you did? Oh, 
yeah. He invited me over to his house. I went over to

37:30.771 --> 37:31.733
see him. I spent about 45 minutes with him. Oh, 
where is he? He's in Washington. He may eventually

37:36.919 --> 37:42.266
be in Texas.

37:42.286 --> 37:45.490
Why do you say that? He may say, he could, you know, 
accept a position down here someplace.

37:55.163 --> 37:55.223
Um, He was a hell of a guy, a hell of a battalion 
commander.

38:01.046 --> 38:06.092
I know he was promoted because of his relations 
with politicians. He was promoted over about,

38:06.112 --> 38:10.838
what, two or three hundred senior people. Oh, 
yeah. Was there some envy or jealousy or

38:12.660 --> 38:15.444
grumbling? Always some. Always, yeah, always 
some. Like the President's Chief of Staff. He's

38:21.231 --> 38:22.592
out of Class of 50. Shire Meyer, he was The black 
secretary jumped him over several hundred.

38:35.865 --> 38:41.493
Those things happened.

38:41.513 --> 38:55.332
But again,

38:41.513 --> 38:55.332
you see, you must support the system and the 
authority of the President of the United States or

38:41.513 --> 38:55.332
you've got nothing. you have absolutely nothing 
and no security you've got to do that within the

38:56.712 --> 39:04.864
armed forces. Now let's talk about this job 
itself. You're in a political position here.

39:12.336 --> 39:16.142
You're an assistant secretary. This is, you know, 
the deputy secretary or assistant secretary is—

39:24.050 --> 39:25.371
political appointee. That's true. And not a 
military position. This is really rare in

39:28.996 --> 39:33.561
American history. That's true. This might be the 
first case. You must have had, being in this

39:38.626 --> 39:49.579
political slot, and being a colonel, you must have 
had generals who were superior. Is that not true?

39:52.021 --> 39:52.622
That's true. I'm surprised you didn't have to 
resign your commission for this.

40:01.987 --> 40:06.051
Tell me about the difficulty that you had, or the 
position itself. I tell you, I guess

40:06.071 --> 40:21.748
that it does seem

40:06.071 --> 40:21.748
somewhat

40:25.593 --> 40:27.176
out of order in the system.

40:30.281 --> 40:41.639
However,

40:30.281 --> 40:41.639
I guess it's the techniques you use and how you 
avoid disorder and try to gain confidence and

40:30.281 --> 40:41.639
cooperation.

40:45.145 --> 40:48.090
And I've prepared many memorandums. 
particularly on the reserves, and sent to the

40:48.762 --> 41:08.271
Secretary of the Army, and the Navy, and the Air 
Force, and which were directive in nature that the

40:48.762 --> 41:08.271
four-star generals and the three-star generals 
probably didn't like worth a damn. But all they had

41:08.291 --> 41:16.002
to do was to complain to their secretary, and he 
could go complain to Mr. McNamara and get thrown

41:08.291 --> 41:16.002
out

41:19.660 --> 41:48.368
so you see when you ask me about Mr. McNamara

41:19.660 --> 41:48.368
when you work for him and he supports you you have 
